// Semantic direction:
// keypair holds a matched public_key and private_key; generate_keypair produces a fresh pair.
// zeroize_private overwrites the private key bytes after use to prevent memory leakage.
// rsa_oaep is the secure RSA encryption scheme; rsa_pkcs1v15_encrypt is legacy and discouraged.
// oaep_hash is the hash function (SHA-256 or SHA-384) used in OAEP padding.
// rsa_pss is the secure RSA signature scheme; pss_salt_len controls randomness.
// curve_p256 (NIST P-256) and curve_p384 are the standard production elliptic curves.
// curve_secp256k1 is used in Bitcoin and Ethereum signature schemes.
// ec_point_mul computes scalar × point on the curve; this is the core ECC operation.
// ecdsa_sign produces a (r, s) signature; der_encode_sig serializes it for wire formats.
// ed25519 uses the Edwards-curve signature scheme: faster, safer, and smaller than ECDSA.
// ed25519_sign is deterministic (no random nonce needed), eliminating a class of implementation flaws.
// x25519 is the Diffie-Hellman function on Curve25519 for key agreement.
// x25519_dh computes the shared_secret given own private key and peer's public key.
// dh_exchange is the two-message protocol: each party sends their public key, computes shared_secret.
// ecdh performs the same exchange over NIST curves.
// hybrid_encrypt combines asymmetric and symmetric: KEM encapsulates a symmetric key, AEAD encrypts data.
// kem_encapsulate generates a shared_secret and a ciphertext sent to the recipient.
// kem_decapsulate recovers shared_secret from the ciphertext using the private key.
// wrap_with_kem is the full hybrid pattern: kem_encapsulate → aead_encrypt with shared_secret.

// Primitive flow:
// key generation: generate_keypair(curve_p256 or ed25519) -> public_key + private_key
// signing (ed25519): ed25519_sign(private_key, message) -> signature
//   verify: ed25519_verify(public_key, message, signature) -> bool
// signing (ECDSA): ecdsa_sign(private_key, hash(message)) -> (r, s) -> der_encode_sig
//   verify: ecdsa_verify(public_key, hash(message), der_decode_sig(sig))
// key agreement (X25519): alice = x25519_keypair; bob = x25519_keypair
//   alice_shared = x25519_dh(alice.private, bob.public)
//   bob_shared = x25519_dh(bob.private, alice.public)
//   assert alice_shared == bob_shared -> shared_secret
// hybrid encryption: kem_encapsulate(recipient_pub) -> (kem_ct, shared_secret)
//   aead_encrypt(shared_secret, plaintext) -> ciphertext
//   send: kem_ct || ciphertext
//   receive: kem_decapsulate(private_key, kem_ct) -> shared_secret
//            aead_decrypt(shared_secret, ciphertext) -> plaintext

// This defines asymmetric cryptography: RSA, ECDSA, Ed25519, X25519 Diffie-Hellman,
// and hybrid encryption with KEM.
